title: Brian Auger & The Trinity - 2 Albums
description:
2 albums by this great band.  

Definitely What! is a very ambitious album recorded during the fertile period while the band was involved with Julie Driscoll. Includes an instrumental version of The Beatle's "A Day In The Life", two great vocals by Brian Auger, "George Bruno Money "and "Far Horizon" plus riveting interpretations of Wes Montgomerey's "Bumpin' On Sunset" and Booker T & The MG's "Red Beans and Rice".  

Befour features the world debut of guitarist Gary Boyle who went on to form the incredible band Isotope.  Gary shines on their arrangement of Gabriel Faure's "Pavane", Herbie Hancock's "Maiden Voyage", and Eddie Harris' "Listen Here" which features an incredible drum ensemble that includes Mickey Waller form The Jeff Beck Group.

Enjoy and please seed!;-}

Junco
